story.title: Text Nerdy to Me - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: A wild night in Vegas results in a tryst she can’t remember, and a man she can’t forget.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Sabrina York is the New York Times and USA Today bestselling author of snarky, steamy romance.

story.prePaywallNotification: What?! Will was texting the wrong number all along? Tap back into Hooked to see if Erin keeps talking to him anyway.
story.postPaywallNotification: Uh-oh… Is there trouble in paradise already? Tap back into Hooked to see if Will texts Erin back.

messages.text: So…what are you going to do?
I should. It’s the right thing to do.
I’d play with him a little.
If you’re as daring as you say, why wouldn’t you?
Because someone gave him a WRONG number at a bar.
If he were such a catch…
Don’t you think SHE would have made sure she got her number right?
The way I see it is…
I still say you should play with him a little.
Sorry. My roomie was distracting me.
Erin pushes all thoughts of Charlie away.
She needs to be a wild child.
Okay. But should I be jealous?
When can we get together again?
I don’t think that’s such a good idea.
What? You’re breaking my heart here.
We should get to know each other better first.
I thought we hit it off last night.
No pressure — let’s start from scratch.
Okay. What do you look like?
Hey! You said we could start from scratch.
Okay. I’m 6’5” with curly black hair and brown eyes.
What do you do for a living?
I work for a tech company.
None of the tech guys I know have muscles.
Now I scrimmage on weekends with my buddies at Green Lake Park.
She looks back down at her phone.
Don’t you even remember the town we were in?
We’re just starting from scratch, remember?
You’ll think it’s boring. Most people do.
I told you my boring tech stuff.
The least you can do is reciprocate.
I promise to try to stay awake.
All right. I teach history at UW.
No, but I bet you’d make it interesting.
I teach one class comparing British history to Game of Thrones archetypes.
OMG. I would totally take that class.
Right? GOT is a perfect allegory. Mad Kings. Northern walls to keep the berserkers out…
Sorry. I tend to ramble on.
I love it. Something for us to talk about when we meet next.
Well your name, for starters. You never gave it to me last night.
Erin. I like that — it suits you.
I have a brother and a sister.
We should set up a play date.
I thought we were getting to know each other better before we met?
See? You know nothing about me.
If I roll out of bed before noon, I burst into flames.
How do you have a job?
I still think we should meet tomorrow.
You didn’t mention you were leaving town.
Be honest. Are you blowing me off?
You sure? Because I’m getting that vibe.
It’s okay — maybe it was just a flirty thing for you.
If it was, then why do you seem so upset?
Sorry. I’m not very good at this.
Getting to know someone over text message.
You know I have a brother and a sister and a Rottie named Ghost.
I told you I’m a fan.
LOL, I was just surprised at the coincidence. My dog’s name is Nymeria.
Hmm. Maybe we shouldn’t have a play date.
Who knows what mischief those two could get up to?
Overthrowing the evil queen, at the very least.
So…is this the part where I ask what you’re wearing?
Depends if you can handle the answer.
I just rolled out of bed, so I’m in flannel pjs.
Nope. Nekked as a jay bird.
Do you want to see a selfie?
As soon as she asks herself that…
She knows it’s a stupid question.
Fine. But I’m wearing my shirt.
Erin takes a playful selfie of her abdomen.
Tiffany catches her right as she hits send.
What if you look different from the girl from last night?
I’m just too busy drooling to respond.
I told you that you were gorgeous.
Erin looks up from her phone, turning to Tiffany.
Phew — she must be built like me.
I got caught up in the moment, so I forgot we’ve never met!
Tiffany glances at the image of Will’s abs on Erin’s phone.
Holy shit! No wonder you lost all sanity.
You can’t actually meet him now.
Because the minute he sees your face, he’s going to know…
You’re not the girl he met last night.
You may as well just give him to me now.
